          {
            "text": " in a bowl, sprinkle over the bicarbonate of soda, and pour over the boiling water. Stir briefly and leave for 15 minutes until the dates are very soft and the water has turned dark brown.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the batter and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C conventional. Grease a 900 g loaf tin and line with baking paper. Beat the butter and sugar until combined. Beat in the eggs one at a time. Fold in the flour, then stir in the vanilla and the date mixture (liquid included), mashing the dates roughly with a fork as you go. The batter will be loose and dark. Pour into the tin and bake for 42 to 48 minutes until a skewer comes out clean, the top feels firm, and the edges have pulled from the tin. Leave in the tin on a wire rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the sauce and finish",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the butter, cream, and sugar in a saucepan over medium heat, stirring until the butter melts and the sugar dissolves. Bring to a gentle boil and cook for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring, until the sauce thickens slightly and coats the back of a spoon. While the cake is still in the tin, prick the top all over with a skewer and pour over half the sauce. Leave for 10 minutes to absorb, then turn out. Serve with the remaining sauce poured over each slice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
